        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 3:12PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 312 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sanville, or near Bassett, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Martinsville...
Spencer...
Bassett...
Villa Heights...
Chatmoss...
Collinsville...
and Horse Pasture.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
